      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey can u explain quantum entanglement to me? like in plain english i have an exam coming up. also whats the difference between that and just like regular correlation?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Quantum entanglement is a bizarre connection between two or more particles, like a pair of magical, linked coins. When these particles are entangled, they become so intertwined that measuring a property of one instantly tells you the corresponding property of the other, no matter how far apart they are.  The difference from regular correlation is that with entanglement, the particles don't have a definite state *until* you measure one of them; it's like they are both undecided until you look. This instantaneous link is what makes it so weird, even to scientists! Good luck with your exam!",
      "source": "target",
